    <h2>Best Types of Magnesium for Sleep (Compared)</h2>

    <p>Not all magnesium is the same. There are over a dozen commercially available forms, and they differ dramatically in bioavailability, side effect profile, and efficacy for sleep. Choosing the wrong form — like magnesium oxide — means you absorb a fraction of the dose and experience unnecessary gastrointestinal side effects. The table below compares every relevant form so you can make an informed decision.</p>

