    <!-- SECTION 5: DOSAGE -->
    <h2>How Much Magnesium Should You Take for Sleep?</h2>

    <p>Dosage is critical. Too little magnesium has no measurable effect on sleep. Too much causes GI distress and can be dangerous for people with kidney impairment. The clinical trials that demonstrated sleep benefits used 200-500mg of elemental magnesium daily. The sweet spot for most adults is 200-400mg of elemental magnesium taken 1-2 hours before bed.</p>

