    <div class="warn-box">
      <span class="warn-box-ico">⚠️</span>
      <p><strong>Important: NIH Upper Limit.</strong> The Tolerable Upper Intake Level (UL) for supplemental magnesium is 350mg/day for adults — this applies to magnesium from supplements and medications only, not from food. Exceeding this level increases the risk of diarrhea, nausea, and abdominal cramping. People with kidney disease should not take magnesium supplements without physician supervision, as the kidneys are responsible for excreting excess magnesium. <strong>Source: NIH Office of Dietary Supplements.</strong></p>
