    <!-- SECTION 6: TIMING -->
    <h2>When to Take Magnesium for Sleep</h2>

    <p>Timing your magnesium dose correctly can meaningfully improve its effectiveness for sleep. Based on the pharmacokinetics of magnesium absorption and the clinical trial protocols that produced the strongest sleep outcomes, here is the optimal timing protocol:</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="clock" size={22} /></div>
        <h3>1-2 Hours Before Bed</h3>
        <p>Take your magnesium dose 60-120 minutes before your target bedtime. This allows time for intestinal absorption and for magnesium to begin activating GABA receptors and lowering cortisol. Taking it at the exact moment you get into bed is too late for optimal effect.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="coffee" size={22} /></div>
        <h3>With or Without Food</h3>
        <p>Magnesium glycinate can be taken on an empty stomach without GI issues. Magnesium citrate is better absorbed with food to minimize laxative effects. If you experience any stomach discomfort, take your magnesium with a small snack.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="calendar" size={22} /></div>
        <h3>Consistency Is Critical</h3>
        <p>Magnesium works best when taken daily. The clinical trials showing significant sleep improvements ran for 8 weeks of daily dosing. Occasional or sporadic use will not produce the same results. Build magnesium into your nightly routine.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="alert-triangle" size={22} /></div>
        <h3>Avoid Combining with Certain Medications</h3>
        <p>Take magnesium at least 2 hours apart from antibiotics (tetracyclines, fluoroquinolones), bisphosphonates, and thyroid medications. Magnesium can reduce the absorption of these drugs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <span class="tip-box-ico">💡</span>
      <p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Pair magnesium with a warm, caffeine-free beverage as part of a wind-down routine. The combination of magnesium supplementation + consistent sleep timing + reduced screen exposure 1 hour before bed produces significantly better results than any single intervention alone. Sleep hygiene amplifies magnesium's effects.</p>
    </div>

